question.text: The two gases making highest relative contribution to the greenhouse gases are

options.text: <math><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">F</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">s</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant="normal">a</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">n</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi><mo> </mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">N</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi></math>

solution.text: The greenhouse is the naturally occurring phenomenon that is responsible for heating of earth's surface and atmosphere. Gases like carbondioxide and methane are commonly called as greenhouse gases. The relative contribution of various greenhouse gases to total global warming is <math><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">O</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2: </mn></mrow></msub><mn>0</mn><mi mathvariant="normal">%</mi><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4: </mn></mrow></msub><mn>20</mn><mi mathvariant="normal">%</mi><mo>, </mo></math><math><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">F</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">C</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">s:</mi><mo> </mo><mn>14</mn><mi mathvariant="normal">%</mi><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">N</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant="normal">O: </mi><mn>6</mn><mi mathvariant="normal">%</mi></math>.
